node.title: The most important thing to grow your business

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 16, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou I'm 31 years old and I'm still figuring this out... But think the way we view life is a little broken (a thread)'.

node.text:
What makes you happy, motivated, and inspired?

Do you remember when you were a kid and had crazy dreams?

Maybe you wanted to be an actor, an astronaut, a billionaire…

Thinking that anything is possible makes life magical.

But as you grew older, more and more people were skeptical towards your dream.

Suddenly they told you:

Be more realistic…

Get a real job…

Nobody can make a living doing that…

It’s too hard…

So you buried your dream in the back of your head.

And did what society told you to do.

But it never got easier.

You never “learned to love” your job.

And that is a good thing. 

Because life is not about “learning to love” your job.

You already have things you love, and that’s what you should do in life.

The good news is, it’s never too late.

You can still be, do and achieve anything you want.

I believe in you.

If you want to find out how I created a life where I can do anything I want…

By starting my own Amazon business…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity 
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

...and discover how it can do the same for you.

node.text:
There's ONE thing rich people always do but you don't:

Confidently asking for help, resources and support. 

I'm not talking about begging, or demanding free hand-outs.

I mean having a vision they are burning for …

A passion so strong that others WANT to be a part of it…

And when a passionate person, who is fully convinced their vision will come true, asks for something…

You can only say yes.

That's a quality that can make people successful.

But most people are too proud to accept help.

They think doing everything alone is a sign of strength. 

But this is complete BS. 

If this were true, no entrepreneur would need a team.

No company would need employees. 

Even Jesus had his apostles.

So don’t be so arrogant to believe you can do something new on your own without failing first. 

If you're ready to accent help in building a business and changing your life, 

follow 👉@bjkuniversity 
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And they'll show you everything you need.

node.text:
You can change!

Sometimes change can feel slow and almost impossible.

Like you are trying hard but there are obstacles left and right.

The thing is, change becomes easy once you realize that you can change at any point in your life.

Maybe you are out of shape. You can decide right now to get up and go for a run.

Maybe you are unhappy with your job. You can decide right now to quit.

Maybe you don’t have supportive people in your life. You can decide right now to meet new people.

Once you made the decision, it’s time to create a new vision for your life.

What do you want the outcome to be?

And once you have that vision, make it your mission to make the vision reality.

It sounds simple but it takes time and dedication.

Change is easier if you’re surrounded by the right people and learn from the right teachers.

If you haven’t found your tribe yet…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity 
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

...and meet our supportive community.

(inspiration: @melrobbins)

node.text:
They are lying to you…

I keep seeing it again and again…

Unrealistic promises.

The “make money online” market is especially full of them.

Gurus telling you you can make millions with their method…

Presumable experts “showing” you how to make $100k by the end of the year…

I get that making money is motivating.

And I want you to be successful and have all the money you need.

But I think it’s time that we become a bit more realistic.

You can definitely make money online. That’s what I do with Amazon.

But it’s still a business. It takes dedication, sacrifices, commitment and time.

So, please don’t enroll in a course and leave your job thinking you will make $10k the next month…

Take your time to learn. 

Build a stable foundation first, then shoot for the moon.

If you understand that building a business takes time and you still want to go for it…

It's true that life teaches us the best lessons but you don't have to live 40 years to learn what's most important. It's best to learn from those who made the experience before you so you can build on their findings and go further beyond then they ever could.

Just like our scientists build on the findings of Newton and Einstein, you can learn from people who have done what you wanna do. 

The only problem is that today, most people don't have the freedom to change what they wanna change.

Call me crazy but it seems that the only way to truly change the world nowadays is to become a business owner. Do you agree?

If you feel the same way and you wanna try building a business as well then I recommend you

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '1. People come and go and that's OK Your best friends can become strangers and strangers can become your best friends- and that happens for a reason: In life, you would always have the people around you that help you get to the next stop on your journey. Some will stay with you until the end and some only are companions for a time. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '2. Your diet isn't just what you eat A healthy body and a healthy mind go hand-in-hand. To be truly healthy, watch your diet, but also what you read, who you talk and what you think. to @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '3. You can't please everyone if you want to be happy Your mental health and happiness always go 1st. Only if you're at your best you can help others be happy and sometimes that means letting people down. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '4. Don't let rejection become self-rejection Everyone will face rejection in their life sooner or later. But even if somebody rejects you you still have value as a person. Don't define yourself by someone else's "no." @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '5. Your past doesn't define your future Even if you had a rough childhood, and life dealt you a bad hand, this doesn't mean that you can't change your future. In fact, you can now choose to react differently, to feel differently and to live differently. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '6. You won't find happiness in other people's dreams If you only work to achieve goals that society says you are supposed to want you will never be happy. It's perfectly okay to have dreams that almost no one agrees with. It's perfectly okay to work on something no one understands as long as it fulfils you. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '7. Everything is up to to you It's uncomfortable to accept that you can take responsibility for everything in your life. But taking ownership gives you the power to truly change your life in any way you want. Never blame others for your misfortune but rather take action to change what you don't want @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity.
